74
00:05:53,230 --> 00:05:59,260
Say yes.

75
00:06:15,630 --> 00:06:17,420
How did it come to this?

76
00:06:21,860 --> 00:06:23,980
I was shooting hoops this afternoon.

77
00:06:26,300 --> 00:06:28,500
How come I was stuck

78
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:29,740
holding the bouquet tonight?

79
00:06:33,740 --> 00:06:34,860
I should've never come.

80
00:06:36,300 --> 00:06:38,060
Even if I did,
I shouldn't have gotten on stage

81
00:06:38,060 --> 00:06:40,500
or responded to the host.

82
00:06:40,860 --> 00:06:43,300
Why do I always say yes to people?

83
00:06:43,740 --> 00:06:45,380
Wu Xiuya, you're such a pushover.

84
00:06:45,380 --> 00:06:47,300
Why not just go be a wishing genie?

85
00:06:47,420 --> 00:06:49,500
Why is it that everyone
who shows up in your life

86
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:50,860
gets to boss you around?

87
00:06:51,060 --> 00:06:52,940
Can't you take charge for once?

88
00:06:53,300 --> 00:06:55,180
Are you living just to be a puppet?

89
00:06:55,180 --> 00:06:56,940
Always letting people pull your strings?

90
00:06:56,940 --> 00:06:58,300
Zheng Hao is exactly what you deserve.

91
00:06:58,300 --> 00:06:59,620
He's never held your hand,

92
00:07:00,060 --> 00:07:01,620
only led you by the nose.

93
00:07:03,620 --> 00:07:06,420
Even the host can dictate your life.

94
00:07:07,980 --> 00:07:10,620
In ancient times, at least
bandits brought swords to abduct women.

95
00:07:10,740 --> 00:07:12,500
A bouquet was all it took to trap me.

96
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:14,500
Why bother using a bouquet?

97
00:07:14,860 --> 00:07:17,380
Might as well just throw Zheng Hao at me.

98
00:07:21,300 --> 00:07:22,980
What kind of couple are we?

99
00:07:22,980 --> 00:07:24,180
After over a week of icing out,

100
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:26,500
the first thing he says is,
"Will you marry me?"

101
00:07:26,620 --> 00:07:27,620
I've never seen anyone

102
00:07:27,620 --> 00:07:29,420
use a proposal to break the ice before.

103
00:07:29,420 --> 00:07:30,940
Are you just doing this for good luck?

104
00:07:31,060 --> 00:07:32,860
How convenient for you,

105
00:07:32,860 --> 00:07:34,420
proposing

106
00:07:34,420 --> 00:07:35,860
on someone else's wedding.

107
00:07:35,860 --> 00:07:37,740
Are you planning to sneak into their...

108
00:07:42,860 --> 00:07:43,740
Zheng Hao, do you think

109
00:07:43,740 --> 00:07:45,740
you're some kind of hero today?

110
00:07:45,980 --> 00:07:47,180
Puffed up chest,

111
00:07:47,180 --> 00:07:48,420
one knee on the ground,

112
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:50,380
strutting around like a proud rooster

113
00:07:50,380 --> 00:07:51,940
crowing to the world.

114
00:07:53,300 --> 00:07:54,500
"Today I'm engaged.

115
00:07:55,420 --> 00:07:56,260
Xiuya,

116
00:07:56,710 --> 00:07:57,860
marry me.

117
00:07:58,300 --> 00:08:00,620
This is all for you."

118
00:08:00,620 --> 00:08:01,860
Are you crazy?

119
00:08:01,980 --> 00:08:03,620
This is someone else's wedding.

120
00:08:04,620 --> 00:08:07,060
Funny how you think about work
even when proposing.

121
00:08:07,860 --> 00:08:09,980
Does your department
give marriage bonuses?

122
00:08:10,420 --> 00:08:12,180
On our wedding, are we going
to bow first to heaven,

123
00:08:12,180 --> 00:08:13,020
then to the chairman,

124
00:08:13,030 --> 00:08:14,420
and finally to the stock market?

125
00:08:14,420 --> 00:08:15,620
Are you marrying me,

126
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:17,620
or the chairman?

127
00:08:17,860 --> 00:08:19,860
This proposal isn't really for me.

128
00:08:20,060 --> 00:08:21,300
I'm just your accessory,

129
00:08:21,530 --> 00:08:23,300
the prop you use to show others

130
00:08:23,300 --> 00:08:24,940
how successful you are.

131
00:08:25,620 --> 00:08:28,060
Zheng Hao said since we work
at the same company,

132
00:08:28,060 --> 00:08:29,740
someone has to make sacrifices.

133
00:08:29,740 --> 00:08:31,980
But in these two years with him,

134
00:08:31,980 --> 00:08:33,010
I've done nothing but sacrifice.

135
00:08:33,100 --> 00:08:33,980
Some of you even say

136
00:08:33,980 --> 00:08:35,980
I got in through connections
with Zheng Hao's family.

137
00:08:35,980 --> 00:08:38,220
What kind of connection works like this?

138
00:08:38,460 --> 00:08:39,700
For Zheng Hao, I switched departments.

139
00:08:39,820 --> 00:08:41,940
For his aunt's sake,
I swallowed my pride.

140
00:08:42,060 --> 00:08:44,060
To get married,
I can't even work out of town.

141
00:08:44,460 --> 00:08:46,340
People with connections get perks,

142
00:08:46,420 --> 00:08:48,820
but his family took advantage of me.

143
00:08:48,940 --> 00:08:50,580
What are you all cheering for?

144
00:08:50,580 --> 00:08:52,300
What does it have to do with you?

145
00:08:52,620 --> 00:08:53,940
I noticed that when people get together,

146
00:08:53,940 --> 00:08:55,340
they like to do two things:

147
00:08:55,540 --> 00:08:56,420
urge others to get married

148
00:08:56,420 --> 00:08:57,310
and watch others jump off buildings.

149
00:08:57,310 --> 00:08:59,420
You just can't stand leaving people
a way out, huh?

150
00:09:00,060 --> 00:09:02,060
Why should I follow your rules?

151
00:09:02,180 --> 00:09:04,060
You don't even like me.

152
00:09:04,060 --> 00:09:05,300
You like Mrs. Zheng-Wu

153
00:09:05,300 --> 00:09:06,460
who covers shifts,

154
00:09:06,460 --> 00:09:07,700
takes the blame,

155
00:09:07,700 --> 00:09:10,580
and does whatever you ask.

156
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:13,460
Well, guess what?

157
00:09:13,460 --> 00:09:15,470
Stop calling me Zheng Hao's girlfriend.

158
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:16,700
My name is Wu Xiuya.

159
00:09:16,940 --> 00:09:18,580
And stop calling him Zheng Hao.

160
00:09:18,940 --> 00:09:19,780
Call him

161
00:09:21,220 --> 00:09:22,060
the Rooster.

162
00:09:22,460 --> 00:09:23,300
(Suddenly,)

163
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:24,460
(in that moment,)

164
00:09:24,940 --> 00:09:27,060
(Wu Xiuya comes to her senses.)

165
00:09:27,340 --> 00:09:30,180
(She knew what she truly wanted.)

166
00:09:31,580 --> 00:09:32,820
Come on, babe.

167
00:09:36,460 --> 00:09:37,300
Come with me.

168
00:09:38,300 --> 00:09:39,140
Where?

169
00:09:49,580 --> 00:09:54,460
(Happiness)

170
00:09:54,700 --> 00:09:55,940
Thought you weren't coming.

171
00:09:56,460 --> 00:09:57,340
Come in.

172
00:09:57,940 --> 00:09:58,780
Rooster,

173
00:09:59,220 --> 00:10:00,300
I need to talk to you.

174
00:10:02,340 --> 00:10:03,180
What now?

175
00:10:03,220 --> 00:10:04,580
Giving me nicknames now?

176
00:10:05,590 --> 00:10:06,570
I'm breaking up with you.

177
00:10:11,300 --> 00:10:12,460
Wait, what? I don't get it.

178
00:10:12,610 --> 00:10:13,460
Are you drunk?

179
00:10:13,460 --> 00:10:14,940
Maybe you mean something else.

180
00:10:15,820 --> 00:10:17,700
You just said yes to my proposal.

181
00:10:17,820 --> 00:10:18,940
I meant what I said.

182
00:10:18,940 --> 00:10:20,220
No hidden meanings.

183
00:10:21,460 --> 00:10:22,820
I've thought it through.

184
00:10:22,940 --> 00:10:24,820
The woman you're marrying
is not who I really am.

185
00:10:24,970 --> 00:10:26,490
And I don't want
to get married like this.

186
00:10:28,140 --> 00:10:29,240
We're done.

187
00:10:30,260 --> 00:10:31,860
You'll find someone better for you.

188
00:10:40,100 --> 00:10:42,100
Wow.

189
