=Episode 5=

196
00:11:12,340 --> 00:11:16,100
Today's the first day of my new life.

197
00:11:34,100 --> 00:11:35,100
The same flavor.

198
00:11:37,820 --> 00:11:39,700
Zheng Hao never let me wear shorts,

199
00:11:40,460 --> 00:11:42,460
said it looks unprofessional.

200
00:11:43,940 --> 00:11:44,820
Does it?

201
00:11:45,580 --> 00:11:47,940
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

202
00:12:03,340 --> 00:12:04,700
Do you like this red dress?

203
00:12:04,940 --> 00:12:05,820
Wanna try it on?

204
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:09,160
Nah, I'm a little hungry.

205
00:12:09,180 --> 00:12:10,020
Let's go.

206
00:12:29,300 --> 00:12:30,300
Impressive.

207
00:12:33,060 --> 00:12:34,540
Nice shot!

208
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:47,900
Xiuya.

209
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:48,740
Wait a minute.

210
00:12:49,180 --> 00:12:50,020
Let's take a break.

211
00:12:57,420 --> 00:12:58,260
Got it?

212
00:12:58,270 --> 00:12:59,120
Yeah.

213
00:12:59,140 --> 00:13:00,420
- Come on.
- Let's go.

214
00:13:01,060 --> 00:13:01,900
Take it.

215
00:13:11,660 --> 00:13:13,660
Boba just tastes better here at home.

216
00:13:13,790 --> 00:13:15,320
This is nice.

217
00:13:19,300 --> 00:13:20,180
Oh no. Darn it.

218
00:13:20,180 --> 00:13:21,660
Video call from my mom.

219
00:13:21,660 --> 00:13:23,180
She doesn't know I'm back.

220
00:13:24,420 --> 00:13:25,540
Come help me.

221
00:13:25,540 --> 00:13:26,660
Come here. Hurry.

222
00:13:27,180 --> 00:13:28,060
Block the window.

223
00:13:28,060 --> 00:13:29,180
It's nighttime there.

224
00:13:29,180 --> 00:13:30,420
- Nighttime.
- Okay, okay.

225
00:13:32,300 --> 00:13:33,500
- Is this okay?
- Yes.

226
00:13:38,420 --> 00:13:39,660
What's up, Mom?

227
00:13:40,540 --> 00:13:42,540
Why did you take so long to answer again?

228
00:13:42,540 --> 00:13:43,540
I was so worried.

229
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:46,660
Going to bed so early?

230
00:13:47,020 --> 00:13:47,860
Are you sick?

231
00:13:48,060 --> 00:13:48,900
No.

232
00:13:49,590 --> 00:13:52,900
I stayed up late
working on my thesis last night.

233
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:54,780
I'm exhausted.

234
00:13:55,300 --> 00:13:57,780
Don't stay up late.

235
00:13:57,900 --> 00:14:00,820
You can't ignore your health
just because you're young.

236
00:14:00,820 --> 00:14:02,820
You'll regret it when you get older.

237
00:14:04,300 --> 00:14:05,300
I got it, Mom.

238
00:14:05,880 --> 00:14:06,780
I'll hang up now.

239
00:14:06,780 --> 00:14:08,300
I'll call you tomorrow.

240
00:14:08,780 --> 00:14:09,620
Just hang on.

241
00:14:09,660 --> 00:14:12,500
I'm running out of my skincare set here.

242
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:14,180
Buy me two more sets,

243
00:14:14,180 --> 00:14:16,060
and one for Ms. Zhang too.

244
00:14:16,420 --> 00:14:18,900
Mom, I'm busy lately.

245
00:14:19,180 --> 00:14:21,260
Why don't you just buy it back home?

246
00:14:21,260 --> 00:14:24,060
The discounts are even better
than abroad.

247
00:14:24,660 --> 00:14:25,500
Xiaolan,

248
00:14:25,900 --> 00:14:28,420
just buy a few more sets there.

249
00:14:28,540 --> 00:14:29,380
Your mom...

250
00:14:29,420 --> 00:14:30,540
Be quiet.

251
00:14:30,900 --> 00:14:31,780
Sorry.

252
00:14:32,060 --> 00:14:33,540
Did I wake you up?

253
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:35,780
It's my mom and dad.

254
00:14:36,020 --> 00:14:37,420
I'm hanging up.

255
00:14:37,780 --> 00:14:38,900
Let's hang up now.

256
00:14:39,060 --> 00:14:40,180
They're asleep.

257
00:14:40,180 --> 00:14:41,540
I'll call you back later.

258
00:14:44,570 --> 00:14:45,420
Done?

259
00:14:45,420 --> 00:14:46,260
Yeah.

260
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:49,140
Wait,

261
00:14:49,420 --> 00:14:50,780
what's going on?

262
00:14:51,180 --> 00:14:52,780
Your parents don't know you're back?

263
00:14:52,900 --> 00:14:55,420
Of course not. I snuck back.

264
00:14:55,420 --> 00:14:57,420
But you'll get busted easily.

265
00:14:58,300 --> 00:15:00,780
You have no idea how smart I am.

266
00:15:00,780 --> 00:15:01,780
All of my money

267
00:15:01,780 --> 00:15:03,300
is on my credit card.

268
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:05,540
But whenever I use it,

269
00:15:05,540 --> 00:15:06,790
my dad gets a notification.

270
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:07,900
So, to keep them from finding out,

271
00:15:07,900 --> 00:15:09,900
I transferred the money
from my credit card

272
00:15:09,900 --> 00:15:11,780
to my domestic debit card.

273
00:15:12,060 --> 00:15:13,420
But now, even to buy toothpaste,

274
00:15:13,420 --> 00:15:14,500
I have to order from websites abroad

275
00:15:14,500 --> 00:15:16,380
and have it shipped here.

276
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:18,180
That cost a lot.

277
00:15:18,420 --> 00:15:19,900
With the little money I have left,

278
00:15:20,140 --> 00:15:21,780
I don't know how long I can last.

279
00:15:23,300 --> 00:15:25,300
Then why bother coming back?

280
00:15:25,310 --> 00:15:27,580
You know I'm not cut out for studying.

281
00:15:27,580 --> 00:15:29,060
If I took the college entrance exam here,

282
00:15:29,060 --> 00:15:31,420
I'd only get into a third-rate university.

283
00:15:31,420 --> 00:15:33,000
But my dad insisted on spending a fortune

284
00:15:33,160 --> 00:15:35,180
to get me into a grad school in the US.

285
00:15:35,180 --> 00:15:36,940
He's just buying bragging rights.

286
00:15:36,940 --> 00:15:38,350
He goes around showing off,

287
00:15:38,710 --> 00:15:42,640
"My daughter is doing postgrad
in the US, so impressive!"

288
00:15:42,780 --> 00:15:43,660
He has no idea

289
00:15:43,660 --> 00:15:45,240
that with my current grades,

290
00:15:45,380 --> 00:15:48,240
I'll be expelled in the second year.

291
00:15:48,380 --> 00:15:49,500
So what are you going to do?

292
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:50,820
That's why I came back.

293
00:15:51,380 --> 00:15:52,660
I realized

294
00:15:53,060 --> 00:15:55,060
that whether I do well in school or not,

295
00:15:55,060 --> 00:15:56,750
I'll eventually have to come home

296
00:15:56,760 --> 00:15:58,420
and take over my dad's factory.

297
00:15:58,820 --> 00:16:01,660
So I plan to enjoy life here for a year,

298
00:16:01,810 --> 00:16:04,410
then go back to the US
and get a fake diploma

299
00:16:04,420 --> 00:16:06,680
to feed my dad's ego.

300
00:16:07,580 --> 00:16:08,420
Everyone's happy.

301
00:16:08,420 --> 00:16:09,500
But why do you have

302
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:11,060
to take over your dad's factory?

303
00:16:11,060 --> 00:16:12,580
Do you even like that kind of work?

304
00:16:14,300 --> 00:16:16,660
I don't know what I like.

305
00:16:16,820 --> 00:16:18,380
I don't have any big dreams.

306
00:16:18,660 --> 00:16:19,660
But for now,

307
00:16:19,660 --> 00:16:21,580
going home
and taking over the factory seems like

308
00:16:21,580 --> 00:16:23,420
the most readily available
and best option.

309
00:16:23,580 --> 00:16:24,540
Anyway, my dad's still got it

310
00:16:24,540 --> 00:16:26,380
and will be capable for decades to come.

311
00:16:26,380 --> 00:16:28,380
I'll just coast along with him,

312
00:16:28,380 --> 00:16:31,060
get a high salary without
too much effort. How great is that?

313
00:16:35,420 --> 00:16:36,820
This is the place I was telling you about,

314
00:16:37,180 --> 00:16:38,660
where I do stand-up.

315
00:16:39,140 --> 00:16:40,820
(Banghe Bar)

316
00:16:41,060 --> 00:16:41,900
Banker?

317
00:16:43,260 --> 00:16:44,100
It's Banghe.

318
00:16:45,060 --> 00:16:47,080
Just brush up on your reading.

319
00:16:47,980 --> 00:16:48,820
Okay.

320
00:16:51,480 --> 00:16:52,380
Welcome.

321
00:16:53,580 --> 00:16:56,420
This bar is pretty deserted.

322
00:16:58,820 --> 00:17:00,060
Which one of these two is the owner?

323
00:17:00,580 --> 00:17:01,820
- Him?
- Yes.

324
00:17:01,820 --> 00:17:03,380
He's the owner

325
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:05,700
and runs the stand-up comedy club.

326
00:17:06,220 --> 00:17:08,340
Can I hear you do stand-up tonight?

327
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:09,580
You want to?

328
00:17:09,580 --> 00:17:10,580
I do.

329
00:17:12,580 --> 00:17:15,580
- I'll ask the boss if I can get on the list.
- Great.

330
00:17:19,140 --> 00:17:19,980
You're here.

331
00:17:20,020 --> 00:17:21,060
Excuse me.

332
00:17:22,700 --> 00:17:23,540
I'll take this way.

333
00:17:25,700 --> 00:17:26,940
- Wait, what...
- No.

334
00:17:27,580 --> 00:17:28,580
It's stuck. Don't move.

335
00:17:28,700 --> 00:17:30,060
- Wait.
- My hair.

336
00:17:30,340 --> 00:17:31,340
Come with me first, come on.

337
00:17:31,340 --> 00:17:32,260
Come with you?

338
00:17:32,260 --> 00:17:33,700
This way.

339
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:34,700
- Go right.
- Which way?

340
00:17:34,700 --> 00:17:35,540
To your right.

341
00:17:35,700 --> 00:17:37,100
Excuse me.

342
00:17:37,340 --> 00:17:38,340
I'm sorry.

343
00:17:38,340 --> 00:17:39,580
Here. Excuse me.

344
00:17:39,660 --> 00:17:40,500
Just grab it yourself.

345
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:41,340
I'm so sorry.

346
00:17:41,940 --> 00:17:42,980
Is it undone? Let me.

347
00:17:42,980 --> 00:17:44,220
No, it's tangled.

348
00:17:44,620 --> 00:17:46,060
- Come with me. This way.
- Where?

349
00:17:46,810 --> 00:17:47,680
I'm sorry.

350
00:17:47,700 --> 00:17:48,700
This way, please.

351
00:17:48,700 --> 00:17:49,980
- Where?
- To your left.

352
00:17:49,980 --> 00:17:50,820
My left.

353
00:17:50,830 --> 00:17:51,680
Your left. Come on.

354
00:17:51,700 --> 00:17:53,260
Slow down. It hurts.

355
00:17:53,260 --> 00:17:54,100
Let's walk together.

356
00:17:54,260 --> 00:17:55,700
One, two.

357
00:17:56,060 --> 00:17:57,540
One, two.

358
00:17:57,820 --> 00:17:59,500
One, two.

359
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:00,700
Zhiyong.

360
00:18:00,700 --> 00:18:01,700
Give me scissors.

361
00:18:01,700 --> 00:18:02,540
- Scissors?
- Scissors.

362
00:18:02,540 --> 00:18:03,500
No way.

363
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:04,980
You can't cut my hair.

364
00:18:04,980 --> 00:18:06,540
I can't untangle it without cutting.

365
00:18:06,580 --> 00:18:07,980
How did it get tangled like this?

366
00:18:07,980 --> 00:18:09,580
- I'll do it.
- Gosh.

367
00:18:09,580 --> 00:18:11,260
What happened to you two?

368
00:18:11,700 --> 00:18:12,580
Shi Ye.

369
00:18:12,700 --> 00:18:13,700
- Ouch.
- Time to go on stage.

370
00:18:14,700 --> 00:18:15,700
Don't raise your hand.

371
00:18:16,210 --> 00:18:17,060
It won't stab you.

372
00:18:17,060 --> 00:18:18,460
Be gentle, it hurts.

373
00:18:18,460 --> 00:18:19,700
Okay, okay, I won't move.

374
00:18:22,060 --> 00:18:23,260
Hello everyone, I'm Shi Ye.

375
00:18:26,300 --> 00:18:27,700
Lately, I've noticed

376
00:18:27,700 --> 00:18:29,060
that anxiety-inducing articles

377
00:18:29,300 --> 00:18:31,980
often pop up in my WeChat Moments.

378
00:18:32,060 --> 00:18:33,820
Titles like,

379
00:18:33,980 --> 00:18:36,580
"You've Been Left Behind by Your Peers."

380
00:18:36,820 --> 00:18:38,060
I think 90% of people

381
00:18:38,060 --> 00:18:39,700
probably feel like

382
00:18:39,700 --> 00:18:40,980
they're the ones being left behind.

383
00:18:41,220 --> 00:18:43,260
But I don't think so.

384
00:18:43,340 --> 00:18:45,980
It's like 10 people walking down the road,

385
00:18:46,060 --> 00:18:48,060
and one person is walking faster.

386
00:18:48,700 --> 00:18:49,540
I don't think

387
00:18:49,580 --> 00:18:51,700
that one person abandoned the other nine.

388
00:18:52,060 --> 00:18:53,220
I think the nine

389
00:18:53,220 --> 00:18:54,540
abandoned that one person.

390
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:57,860
At this point, someone would say,

391
00:18:57,860 --> 00:18:59,540
"We have nine people now,

392
00:18:59,940 --> 00:19:00,980
why don't we

393
00:19:00,980 --> 00:19:02,500
draw our own finish line?"

394
00:19:02,500 --> 00:19:03,700
Then someone else would say,

395
00:19:03,700 --> 00:19:04,540
"Right,

396
00:19:04,700 --> 00:19:06,700
I think I live happily every day,

397
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:07,940
so I'm successful."

398
00:19:08,620 --> 00:19:09,980
And another person would say,

399
00:19:09,980 --> 00:19:11,820
"I feel that the person I love loves me back,

400
00:19:11,820 --> 00:19:13,100
so I'm successful."

401
00:19:13,540 --> 00:19:15,140
In the end, everyone draws a finish line

402
00:19:15,140 --> 00:19:16,460
at their own feet.

403
00:19:16,460 --> 00:19:18,260
(This is Zhao Xiaolan's first)

404
00:19:18,620 --> 00:19:21,220
(live comedy show after returning home.)

405
00:19:21,700 --> 00:19:23,260
(In just five minutes,)

406
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:26,380
(she finds herself captivated by Shi Ye.)

407
00:19:26,620 --> 00:19:29,260
(She's captivated
by Shi Ye's humor and talent.)

408
00:19:29,700 --> 00:19:30,540
(Of course,)

409
00:19:30,700 --> 00:19:33,780
(most of all, his charm and good looks.)

410
00:19:34,260 --> 00:19:35,260
I'm Shi Ye. Thank you.

411
00:19:38,620 --> 00:19:39,620
Get ready.

412
00:19:42,100 --> 00:19:43,100
Next up,

413
00:19:43,700 --> 00:19:44,980
we have

414
00:19:44,980 --> 00:19:46,700
a very special guest.

415
00:19:46,860 --> 00:19:48,260
She claims

416
00:19:48,260 --> 00:19:50,500
to have never done stand-up before,

417
00:19:50,500 --> 00:19:51,780
but she's already blown the roof off

418
00:19:51,780 --> 00:19:53,220
twice here at Banghe.

419
00:19:53,220 --> 00:19:56,980
Give it up for the angry office beauty,

420
00:19:57,100 --> 00:19:59,860
Wu Xiuya, with her storm of words.

421
00:20:00,340 --> 00:20:01,300
Here we go.

422
00:20:04,780 --> 00:20:06,500
Hello everyone, I'm Wu Xiuya.

423
00:20:07,620 --> 00:20:09,500
(Banghe Bar)

424
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:10,700
Let me introduce you.

425
00:20:10,980 --> 00:20:11,980
This is Liang Dong.

426
00:20:11,980 --> 00:20:12,980
You can call him Dong.

427
00:20:12,980 --> 00:20:14,700
He's a graduate student

428
00:20:14,700 --> 00:20:16,020
at Ocean University

429
00:20:16,260 --> 00:20:17,700
and a talent I found.

430
00:20:17,700 --> 00:20:19,500
He's been doing stand-up
for less than two months

431
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:20,700
and is catching up to me fast.

432
00:20:21,540 --> 00:20:22,980
I met Xiuya last time.

433
00:20:23,100 --> 00:20:24,460
Well,

434
00:20:24,540 --> 00:20:26,220
this is our first time meeting.

435
00:20:26,220 --> 00:20:28,220
Didn't expect it to be hair-entangling.

436
00:20:28,220 --> 00:20:29,780
Unforgettable.

437
00:20:29,980 --> 00:20:31,980
A grudge forged. I'll remember that.

438
00:20:33,020 --> 00:20:33,860
This here

439
00:20:33,860 --> 00:20:36,540
is the main man of Banghe, Shi Ye.

440
00:20:36,580 --> 00:20:38,300
His career path

441
00:20:38,300 --> 00:20:39,220
is interesting.

442
00:20:39,220 --> 00:20:41,100
He's been a barber,

443
00:20:41,100 --> 00:20:42,780
a photographer, a chef,

444
00:20:42,860 --> 00:20:45,140
even a pet mediator at People's Park.

445
00:20:45,700 --> 00:20:46,700
Those are all side gigs, right?

446
00:20:46,700 --> 00:20:47,980
So what's your main job?

447
00:20:48,100 --> 00:20:49,260
He runs a culture company.

448
00:20:49,700 --> 00:20:52,100
Really? So impressive.

449
00:20:52,380 --> 00:20:54,260
I take all kinds of writing gigs online:

450
00:20:54,260 --> 00:20:55,500
college book reports,

451
00:20:55,500 --> 00:20:56,500
middle school essays,

452
00:20:56,700 --> 00:20:58,140
elementary school parent signatures,

453
00:20:58,380 --> 00:20:59,980
love letters, WeChat Moments posts,

454
00:20:59,980 --> 00:21:00,860
lost cat notices,

455
00:21:00,860 --> 00:21:01,780
and even those

456
00:21:01,780 --> 00:21:03,220
"exposing my ex-boyfriend" posts
on social media.

457
00:21:03,220 --> 00:21:04,060
You name it.

458
00:21:04,260 --> 00:21:05,300
I'm Cao Zhiyong,

459
00:21:05,300 --> 00:21:06,980
the owner of this bar.

460
00:21:06,980 --> 00:21:09,140
Also the bartender,

461
00:21:09,140 --> 00:21:10,500
janitor, cook,

462
00:21:10,700 --> 00:21:11,940
host,

463
00:21:11,940 --> 00:21:13,020
and performer.

464
00:21:13,220 --> 00:21:14,980
Although the bar is small,

465
00:21:14,980 --> 00:21:17,220
it's got everything, right?

466
00:21:17,220 --> 00:21:18,500
Let me tell you,

467
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:20,500
my bar is one of the top clubs
in Shanghai.

468
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:21,860
This circle is so small,

469
00:21:21,860 --> 00:21:22,780
there's no waitlist.

470
00:21:22,780 --> 00:21:24,020
Just open a club

471
00:21:24,020 --> 00:21:25,500
and you're one of the top clubs
in Shanghai.

472
00:21:26,140 --> 00:21:27,020
That being said,

473
00:21:27,020 --> 00:21:28,540
stand-up is booming,

474
00:21:28,540 --> 00:21:30,540
we could be on the Spring Festival Gala
one day, you know?

475
00:21:30,620 --> 00:21:31,580
Come on.

476
00:21:31,580 --> 00:21:33,820
Stand-up and the Gala
are totally incompatible.

477
00:21:33,820 --> 00:21:35,820
It would be so awkward.

478
00:21:36,380 --> 00:21:39,140
I always thought
music and stand-up could mix.

479
00:21:39,140 --> 00:21:40,820
We could do a musical stand-up show.

480
00:21:40,820 --> 00:21:42,580
Or maybe just focus

481
00:21:42,580 --> 00:21:43,540
on improving your stand-up first?

482
00:21:43,540 --> 00:21:45,620
Look at Xiuya, she's only performed twice

483
00:21:45,620 --> 00:21:46,860
- and she's already crushing it.
- Please.

484
00:21:46,860 --> 00:21:48,620
I just stumbled into it.

485
00:21:48,620 --> 00:21:50,380
I barely know what stand-up is.

486
00:21:51,100 --> 00:21:52,100
Don't be modest.

487
00:21:52,140 --> 00:21:53,940
You're killing it.

488
00:21:54,620 --> 00:21:55,820
Next time you come over,

489
00:21:55,860 --> 00:21:57,140
bring a hard drive,

490
00:21:57,140 --> 00:21:58,820
and I'll load it up
with some foreign stand-up.

491
00:21:59,340 --> 00:22:02,100
I can also take you
to some open mics when you have time,

492
00:22:02,100 --> 00:22:03,140
so you can see how it's done.

493
00:22:03,140 --> 00:22:04,820
You'll improve in no time.

494
00:22:05,380 --> 00:22:06,620
It's just a pity

495
00:22:07,060 --> 00:22:09,340
our bartender quit.

496
00:22:09,780 --> 00:22:11,860
Otherwise, I'd have more time.

497
00:22:13,580 --> 00:22:15,100
I could be the bartender.

498
00:22:15,240 --> 00:22:16,180
Aren't you a returnee from overseas?

499
00:22:16,190 --> 00:22:18,140
You're so rich, who could afford you?

500
00:22:18,300 --> 00:22:19,140
Free meals are fine.

501
00:22:20,120 --> 00:22:21,380
Seriously.

502
00:22:24,300 --> 00:22:26,140
Didn't you say
you came back to enjoy life?

503
00:22:26,140 --> 00:22:28,100
Why are you bartending now?

504
00:22:28,100 --> 00:22:29,060
I can do both.

505
00:22:29,060 --> 00:22:30,300
Sleep during the day

506
00:22:30,300 --> 00:22:31,300
and bartend at night.

507
00:22:31,300 --> 00:22:32,540
Make money and have fun.

508
00:22:32,540 --> 00:22:33,380
How great is that?

509
00:22:35,620 --> 00:22:36,700
That's so cool.

510
00:22:37,340 --> 00:22:38,340
Whose RV is this?

511
00:22:38,820 --> 00:22:39,820
Shi Ye's.

512
00:22:39,940 --> 00:22:41,380
Shi Ye's?

513
00:22:42,940 --> 00:22:45,780
That RV is clearly modified.

514
00:22:47,340 --> 00:22:48,540
So cool.

515
00:22:49,140 --> 00:22:52,100
I'm starting to like Shi Ye more.

516
00:22:52,780 --> 00:22:54,940
Are you actually falling for him?

517
00:22:55,060 --> 00:22:56,300
You're such a hopeless romantic.

518
00:22:56,500 --> 00:22:58,020
Don't be so cheesy.

519
00:22:58,140 --> 00:23:00,260
This is me appreciating the beauty of life.

520
00:23:00,260 --> 00:23:01,260
Discover it

521
00:23:01,260 --> 00:23:02,460
and embrace it.

522
00:23:03,100 --> 00:23:04,540
It's great. Watch and learn.

523
00:23:05,060 --> 00:23:05,900
Let's go.

524
00:23:07,140 --> 00:23:08,460
Really nice.

525
00:23:18,820 --> 00:23:21,900
(Zheng Hao: I apologized to Ms. Hu for you.
I'll go get you in the morning. Let's talk.)

526
00:23:27,860 --> 00:23:28,700
Take it.

527
00:23:28,700 --> 00:23:30,500
(Zheng Hao)

528
00:23:31,700 --> 00:23:32,860
Thanks.

529
00:23:33,940 --> 00:23:34,780
Welcome.

530
00:23:34,790 --> 00:23:36,940
All right, I don't have to bartend anymore.

531
00:23:37,060 --> 00:23:38,780
(Zheng Hao)
(While the weekend appeared relaxed,)

532
00:23:39,300 --> 00:23:41,300
(Wu Xiuya's doubts)

533
00:23:41,300 --> 00:23:42,460
(intensified.)

534
00:23:43,580 --> 00:23:45,380
(Happiness)
(Is breaking up really this easy?)

535
00:24:10,540 --> 00:24:11,380
Xiaolan,

536
00:24:12,300 --> 00:24:13,260
something weird happened.

537
00:24:14,060 --> 00:24:14,900
What's wrong?

538
00:24:16,020 --> 00:24:17,060
I returned the ring to Zheng Hao

539
00:24:17,060 --> 00:24:18,100
two nights ago,

540
00:24:18,100 --> 00:24:19,780
but it's back in my bag again.

541
00:24:19,780 --> 00:24:21,060
You saw me return it.

542
00:24:21,060 --> 00:24:21,900
No, I didn't.

543
00:24:22,340 --> 00:24:23,580
How could you not see?

544
00:24:23,580 --> 00:24:24,730
That night, when I told Zheng Hao

545
00:24:24,860 --> 00:24:26,300
I was breaking up with him.

546
00:24:26,300 --> 00:24:28,300
You broke up with him?

547
00:24:28,820 --> 00:24:30,820
Am I in a parallel universe?

548
00:24:31,060 --> 00:24:32,060
That day,

549
00:24:32,390 --> 00:24:33,300
I dragged you

550
00:24:33,300 --> 00:24:35,300
to Zhang Yan's wedding suite door,

551
00:24:35,300 --> 00:24:36,300
called Zheng Hao out,

552
00:24:36,300 --> 00:24:37,670
and told him I've thought it through.

553
00:24:37,670 --> 00:24:39,240
That the woman he's marrying
is not who I really am

554
00:24:39,240 --> 00:24:40,260
and I wanted to break up with him.

555
00:24:40,470 --> 00:24:42,540
Then I returned the ring

556
00:24:42,540 --> 00:24:43,580
and we left.

557
00:24:43,820 --> 00:24:46,300
You did drag me to the suite door

558
00:24:46,300 --> 00:24:47,780
and called Zheng Hao out.

559
00:24:47,780 --> 00:24:49,260
You mumbled something

560
00:24:49,260 --> 00:24:50,110
that I couldn't hear clearly.

